The paper discusses the use of text mining and natural language processing techniques to extract FAQs from sources of software development discussion, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions applying the approach to popular mailing lists, indicating a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and potentially cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions improving the quality of the extracted FAQs, which could involve the use of machine learning (cs.DL).
